ANGULAR - front end technology

Basic Commands :-

1. creating a project - ng new project-name
2. to run angular project  -  ng serve
3. to generate component - ng g c component-name 
4. to create service - ng g s Service-name

Basic Concepts :-

1. Module - to import libraries , - root module - AppModule

2. Components  - to generate ts,html,css , - root component - AppComponent

3. Data Binding - sharing data within a component

    3.1 one way binding - only single directional sharing

        3.1.1   component to view (ts to html)

            3.1.1.1 String Interpolation - {{variable-name}}

            3.1.1.2 Property Binding - [tag-attribute] = "class-property"

        3.1.2   view to component (html to ts)

            3.1.2.1   Event Binding - (event-name) = "function-call"

            3.1.2.2   Event Binding  using $event - (event-name) = "function-call($event)"

            3.1.2.3   Template Referencing variable - syntax: #variable-name

    3.2 Two way binding - same time data sharing in both direction    

        3.2.1  Using ngModel - Import FormsModule -   Import in AppModule

                ngModel - syntax : [(ngModel)] = "variable-name"    
                (set name attribute if it used inside form tag)

4. Component Path Set Up

    router outlet selector

5.  Dependency Injection - Inside Constructor of a class

6.  Angular Service 

7. ngSubmit   - (an event)

8.  Angular Forms
    8.1 Template driven form
    8.2 model driven form -  eg:ReactiveForms - impoet ReactiveFormsModule
        (form group,form array,form control)

9. Directives - to do manipulation in dom

    9.1 component directive

    9.2 structural directive - prefix *
    
        9.2.1   *ngIf
        9.2.2   *ngFor

     9.3 attribute directives   - based on some condition we can apply style
            eg: ngClass 

10. Parent child communication

    10.1 parent-child -@Input()
    10.2 child-parent -@Output()    

